==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: greenmail
<hw>green"mail</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Finance)</fld> <def>The act,
performed by a publicly traded corporation, of paying a corporate raider
to give up a takeover attempt, by buying the shares of stock he owns;
also, the threat posed by corporate raiders to take over a company
unless their stocks are purchased by the company at a price giving them
a large profit.</def> <mark>[Informal]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greenness</ent>⟦br⟧
